node.title: Players must be vaccinated to take part in Australian Open, says tournament director Craig Tiley
node.description: Tournament director Craig Tiley ends speculation over next year's Australian Open, confirming all players — including world number one Novak Djokjovic — must be vaccinated to play at Melbourne Park.

node.title: Victoria records 1,166 new local COVID-19 cases and five deaths
node.description: There are now 9,581 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 458 people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.

node.title: Georgia judge denies defence motion for mistrial in Ahmaud Arbery case
node.description: A Georgia judge has turned down a motion for a mistrial in the Ahmaud Arbery murder case over the impact of Black pastors gathered outside the courthouse.

node.title: Spike in Amazon deforestation draws shock, ups pressure on Brazil
node.description: Diplomats expressed shock and disappointment at new data revealing higher-than-expected deforestation in Brazil's Amazon this year

node.title: Concern and Anger Build Over Missing Athlete’s Sexual Assault Allegations
node.description: The case of Peng Shuai has prompted the women’s tennis tour to rethink its heavy focus in China, where it has threatened to pull events if it cannot verify that she is safe and that her allegations are investigated.

node.title: ‘Woke Left Mob’ Influenced Jury in Trial of Arbery Murder Suspects, Lawyer Says
node.description: The defense lawyer for one of three men accused of murdering Ahmaud Arbery unsuccessfully moved for a mistrial. Closing arguments are scheduled for Monday in Brunswick, Ga.

node.title: Iraq Resistance Warns It's Ready to Expel U.S. by Force at End of Year
node.description: The Iraqi Resistance Coordination Commission said it "did not believe in the seriousness of the occupation and its commitment" to withdrawing combat troops.

node.title: Alex Murdaugh Faces 27 New Charges, Stole From Dead Housekeeper, State Trooper: Prosecutors
node.description: Alex Murdaugh allegedly stole nearly $3.5 million meant as settlement for the sons of his housekeeper who died from a fall in their home in 2019.

node.title: Gov Calls for Renewed Focus on Youth Violence After 2 Shootings Involving Students
node.description: Colorado Governor Jared Polis said the state needs to focus on youth violence after two shootings with high school students happened in Aurora in the same week.

node.title: This is what $1 million will get you in Hobart's hot property market
node.description: This federation home in one of Hobart's premier streets may be "in need of repair" but that isn't deterring those keen to take on the challenge in Tasmania's hot property market.
